    neighborhood: "Monarch Beach",
    detail: "Sub-Zero 685 built-in in a Monarch Beach home — unit running continuously but not maintaining temperature. Condenser coils completely fouled with salt-laden coastal particulate from the ocean-facing bluffs. After coil cleaning, we found the condenser fan motor had also seized from corrosion — replaced with an OEM Sub-Zero motor. Back to temperature within 90 minutes. The homeowner was a part-time resident; the unit had gone unserviced for two years. Salt air doesn't forgive gaps in maintenance.",
    part: "Sub-Zero OEM condenser fan motor + coil cleaning",
    time: "2 hours"
  },
  {
    title: "Wolf range — two burners not lighting, others fine",
    neighborhood: "Strand at Headlands",
    detail: "Wolf 36-inch gas range in a waterfront home at the Headlands — two front burners clicking but not igniting. Classic coastal electrode corrosion. The salt air concentration at the Headlands, sitting right above the water, is among the most aggressive in all of South OC for metal components. Replaced both corroded electrodes with OEM Wolf parts, cleaned and dried the igniter ports, applied protective dielectric grease. Tested all six burners. Advised the homeowner on a yearly electrode inspection given the exposure level.",
    part: "Wolf OEM igniter electrodes x2",
    time: "1.5 hours"
  },
  {
    title: "Wine cooler — temperature inconsistent, wine too warm",
    neighborhood: "Niguel Shores",
    detail: "U-Line 24-inch wine cooler in a Niguel Shores home — temperature swinging 10 degrees above setpoint on warm days. The thermostat control board had drifted out of calibration, a known issue on this U-Line model after 4-5 years. Replaced the control board with an OEM U-Line part, recalibrated, ran temperature verification across 24 hours before leaving a service report. Customer had two dozen bottles of Burgundy at risk — we moved quickly.",
    part: "U-Line OEM thermostat control board",
    time: "1.5 hours"
  },
  {
    title: "Miele dishwasher — F70 error, not draining",
    neighborhood: "Lantern District",
    detail: "Miele G 7566 in a Lantern District renovation — F70 error (water in base tray), anti-flood device triggered. Slow leak at the circulation pump seal had let water into the base. Replaced the pump seal, cleared the base tray, reset the anti-flood sensor, ran multiple cycles to verify. Property was managed by a local property manager who needed it fixed before the next tenant arrived Friday. We prioritized accordingly and had it done Thursday afternoon.",
    part: "Miele OEM circulation pump seal",
    time: "2 hours"
  }
];

const faqs = [
  { q: "Do you offer same-day appliance repair in Dana Point?", a: "Yes — Dana Point is covered by our Irvine Orange County branch. We serve all Dana Point neighborhoods including Monarch Beach, Capistrano Beach, Niguel Shores, and the Lantern District. Call before noon for same-day service in most cases." },
  { q: "Does salt air from the harbor and ocean affect appliances in Dana Point?", a: "Significantly. Dana Point sits directly on the coast, and the marine environment accelerates corrosion on condenser coils, fan motors, and range igniter electrodes faster than anywhere inland. Homes near Monarch Beach, the Headlands, and the harbor are most affected. We recommend condenser coil inspection every 4-6 months for ocean-adjacent properties in Dana Point." },
  { q: "Do you service vacation rentals and second homes in Dana Point?", a: "Yes. A significant portion of Dana Point's housing stock is used as vacation rentals or second homes. We work with property managers and rental management companies regularly." },
  { q: "What brands do you repair in Dana Point?", a: "All major brands. Monarch Beach and the oceanfront neighborhoods tend toward Sub-Zero, Wolf, Miele, and Thermador. The Lantern District and Capistrano Beach have a broader mix. We carry OEM parts for all." },
  { q: "Do you repair wine coolers in Dana Point?", a: "Yes — wine coolers and under-counter refrigeration are common in Dana Point homes. We service Sub-Zero wine columns, U-Line, True, Perlick, and Viking wine units." },
  { q: "What is your diagnostic fee in Dana Point?", a: "Our diagnostic fee is $89. If you proceed with the repair, the $89 is credited against your invoice." },
  { q: "Do you offer a warranty on repairs in Dana Point?", a: "All repairs include a 90-day warranty on parts and labor. Same issue returns within 90 days — we come back at no charge." }
